HOL-3: Function Components and Styling

Function components (recap and expansion)

Declared as regular JavaScript functions that return JSX
Receive data through a single props parameter
Simpler syntax than class components, with no this keyword needed
Ideal for components that mainly display data (like CalculateScore)
Can use Hooks (like useState) to manage state if needed

Applying styles to components

CSS can be written in a separate .css file and imported into a component
Styles are applied using the className attribute in JSX (not class)
Keeping styles in a separate file (like mystyle.css) keeps components clean and readable
Class names in CSS map directly to className values used in JSX
This approach is called external stylesheet styling, as opposed to inline styles

Rendering a component with calculated values

Function components can perform calculations before returning JSX
Values like average = (total/goal) * 100 can be computed inside the function body
The calculated result is inserted into JSX using curly braces { }
This demonstrates how JavaScript logic and UI rendering combine in React
Each time props change, the component re-runs its calculation and re-renders
